definition.value: A type of slash created by taking clips of characters (generally ones not written as gay, or in a relationship together), and through juxtaposition, song choice, and other techniques, portray a slash relationship on screen.
Camp in which mainstream "serious" works are decoded as campy, such as cliché-ridden, badly acted Hollywood films.
Camp which is created by the producers of the text, and not decoded as such by the audience or spectators of the work.
Camp which calls into question dominant notions of gender and sexuality.
Camp which is a result of mainstream appropriation of camp, particularly of queer camp.
A term used, usually derogatory, to describe those whose wealth has been acquired within their own generation, rather than by familial inheritance.
"[T]he inherited wealth of established upper-class families (i.e. gentry, patriciate)" or "a person, family, or lineage possessing inherited wealth".
A person belonging to a social class of upper-class, white American Protestants, usually of British descent (hence Anglo-Saxon). Often abbreviated as "WASP".
Removal of a cisgender man's penis and the testicles, usually non-consensually.
The term can also refer more generally to anything that renders a male less masculine.
An informal fallacy that intends to discredit the opponent's argument by attacking the opponent's own personal behavior as being inconsistent with the argument's conclusion(s).
A variant of the tu quoque logical fallacy that attempts to discredit an opponent's position by charging them with hypocrisy without directly refuting or disproving their argument.

An informal logical fallacy that occurs when two sides of an argument are assumed to have equal or comparable value regardless of their respective merits, which (in turn) can lead to the conclusion that the answer to a problem is always to be found between two extremes.
A category of informal fallacies in which a cause is incorrectly identified.
A fallacy which concludes that persons, groups, or agents generally are inherently inclined to bring about morally fair and fitting consequences.
A version of the just world fallacy in which a person states that they support something that they profess to disagree with because "surely there must be exceptions, right?"
Propaganda which portrays police officers as being strictly friendly and heroic.
A pejorative which is ableist in nature.
Surgical procedures performed on parts of the musculoskeletal system.
Surgical procedures performed on soft tissue.
Surgical removal of soft tissue.
Surgical excision of soft tissue.
Surgical removal of localized subcutaneous fat deposits.
Surgical removal of subcutaneous fat using suction.

A person who is licensed to practiced psychotherapy (psychological therapy), the use of psychological methods, particularly when based on regular personal interaction with adults, to help a person change behavior and overcome problems in desired ways.
A practitioner of sex therapy, a strategy for the improvement of sexual function and treatment of sexual dysfunction.

A subset of sexual practices in which either real or imagined gender background of a participant or participants is used to justify power imbalance, including, but not limited to, the usage of slurs, gendered narratives, and objects imbued with gendered meaning.
Refers to various kinds of slang used by members of the incel (involuntary celibate) community.
A device designed to support a tubular structure, especially the small stainless steel expandable mesh tube inserted within an artery.
Devices that provide support for tubular structures that are being anastomosed or for body cavities during skin grafting.

An instrument used to gently stretch the vagina. They are used when the vagina has become narrowed (vaginal stenosis), such as after brachytherapy for gynecologic cancers, and as therapy for vaginismus and other forms of dyspareunia. Vaginal stents are also routinely used in postoperative care for patients who have undergone vaginoplasty. Frequency of use requirements decrease over time, but remains obligatory lifelong.
A medical device similar to a speculum designed to open and relax the internal/external anal sphincter and rectum originally designed to facilitate medical inspection or relieve constipation.
A pejorative referring to intersex persons.
A pejorative referring to nonbinary persons.
A narrative or visual work featuring a romance between two or more males.

The term shōnen-ai ("boy love") originally connoted ephebophilia or pederasty in Japan, but from the early 1970s to the late 1980s, was used to describe a new genre of shōjo manga, primarily produced by the Year 24 Group of women authors, about beautiful boys in love. Characteristics of shōnen-ai include exoticism, often taking place in Europe, and idealism.

A movement and a form of action against racism and the systemic racism and oppression of marginalized groups. Being antiracist is based on the conscious efforts and actions to provide equitable opportunities for all people on an individual and systemic level.
Any of various kinds of services provide basic human needs relating to quality of life (such as education, health, welfare, etc.).
An activity by an individual or group that aims to influence decisions within political, economic, and social institutions.
The process of defending or pleading the cause of another individual or group.
Advocacy in the interests of social justice, particularly advocacy on the behalf of the disenfranchised or those who have been discriminated against.

Judicial and non-judicial measures implemented in order to redress legacies of human rights abuses.Transitional justice is enacted at a point of political transition from violence and repression to societal stability (or at times years later) and it is informed by a society’s desire to rebuild social trust, repair a fractured justice system, and build a democratic system of governance.
Social policy consists of guidelines, principles, legislation and activities that affect the living conditions conducive to human welfare, such as a person's quality of life.
A policy which positively supports members of disadvantaged or underrepresented groups that have previously suffered discrimination in areas such as education, employment and housing.
The set of social or socio-political negotiations, agreements and actions that aim to solve a specific conflict.

Often this term is used to refer to specific armed conflict resolution; however, in this context it is used for any kind of peaceful (or relatively peaceful) forms of arbitration (or related processes).
The reestablishment of friendly relations; conciliation or rapprochement.
The methods and processes involved in facilitating the peaceful ending of conflict and retribution.
The process of resolving disputes between parties.
Any of a wide range of dispute resolution processes and techniques that act as a means for disagreeing parties to come to an agreement without going through the traditional court system.
A theoretical framework in the social sciences that examines society and culture as they relate to categorizations of race, law, and power.

Works that include publications such as reports, theses, conference papers, translations and limited circulation government documents which are not normally available through commercial publication sources.

A mostly historical mass hysteria which inaccurately suggests that if lesbians are allowed to use bathroom facilities matching their gender identity, that they would sexually harass heterosexual women using those same facilities.
Conventional, formulaic generalizations, opinions, or images based on people who are lesbians.
Conventional, formulaic generalizations, opinions, or images based on people who are transgender.
